Title: Bonganjo Palace
Description: Bonganjo Palace is a historically significant landmark in Buea representing the rich cultural heritage of the Bakweri community The palace served as the residence of the Paramount Chief of Buea acting as a symbol of traditional authority With its unique architecture characterized by intricately carved wooden beams vibrant murals and traditional motifs visitors can immerse themselves in the history and customs of the Bakweri people The palace offers an opportunity to interact with members of the local community who can share captivating tales of their customs traditions and way of life This cultural exchange enhances the visitor experience allowing a deeper understanding and appreciation of the local heritage
